reviews.name: LeeC
reviews.text: I was looking for a replacement for my Saeco Incanto. This was the model I purchased. I like the way it looks, the buttons make sense. It has about half the water tank as my Saeco, and the drip tray holds a lot less (it is U-shaped, with the center hollow): neither one is a deal breaker. My solution was to move it closer to the kitchen sink.
reviews.title: I was looking for a new espresso machine, not a date

reviews.name: EW VINE VOICE
reviews.text: I purchased this to replace a now broken 6 year old Saeco talea giro plus. Unfortunately they no longer make that unit (or else I would have purchased another!), and this one seemed to be the closest equivalent.
reviews.title: closest to what I wanted - small! but small...

reviews.name: Case
reviews.text: Machine makes perfect coffee using beans or ground coffee. Fully automatic, just add the beams on top and Put your cup in place. Coffee always froths it self during the brew which has made me stop adding crème. The steam wand helps add more froth and heat up the coffee. This machine doesn’t make very hot coffee like my Krueig (190F versus 175 F with this machine.)
reviews.title: Buy the optional three or four year insurance for this unit

reviews.name: pianomover75
reviews.text: I am a big time coffee lover and believe it or not a real good cup of coffee is hard to come by these days. I even roast my own coffee beans in an attempt to help achieve that perfect cup at home. I thought I had it ... until I brewed a cup of coffee in the De'Longhi True Brew. This, my friends, doesn't make a good cup of coffee.
reviews.title: De'Longhi True Brew perfection

reviews.name: Terry B.
reviews.text: Great scale for the blind and visual users. Voice is very clear and understandable as well as extremely accurate measurements. I have purchased two of these scales and love them both. I highly recommend them. Side note, one scale lost it voice after several years of use and the company quickly replaced the unit.
reviews.title: Excellent Product

reviews.name: pnBeans
reviews.text: Excellent product! The tara feature is wonderful. I also like the bowl that comes with it; it gives a nice wide flat surface with deep sides. I don't use the bowl all the time, so don't feel like you need to. As I weigh hamburger, I like how I can add and remove meat, as I figure out just the correct weight. Two side notes: the voice is a little loud for my taste, and as a bonus, the product works well with the voice turned off for sighted family members.
reviews.title: Just What I Wanted
